        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36933",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=breich",
                        "name": "breich",
                        "displayName": "Brian Reich",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've worked around this issue by applying the following patch to my Bootstrap:\r\n\r\n<code>\r\n<?php\r\n\r\n\/**\r\n * This file contains the Bootstrap class, which bootstraps resources for the\r\n * SUN Tech Web Services application.\r\n * \r\n * SUN Tech Web Services\r\n * PHP 5.2.9, Zend Framework 1.7.5, ExtJS 2.0\r\n *\r\n * @author    Brian Reich <breich@sun-tech.org>\r\n * @copyright 2008 (C) SUN Area Technical Institute\r\n * @category  Public\r\n * @package   Public\r\n * @version   2.0\r\n *\/\r\n\r\n\/**\r\n * Bootstrap extends Zend_Application_Bootstrap_Bootstrap.\r\n *\/\r\nrequire_once 'Zend\/Application\/Bootstrap\/Bootstrap.php';\r\n\r\nclass Bootstrap extends Zend_Application_Bootstrap_Bootstrap\r\n{\r\n    \/\/ ...\r\n    \r\n    \/**\r\n     * Initializes the Front Controller\r\n     * \r\n     * @return Zend_Controller_Front Returns the Front Controller\r\n     *\/\r\n    protected function _initFrontController()\r\n    {\r\n        $front = Zend_Controller_Front::getInstance();\r\n\r\n        \/\/ ...\r\n\r\n        \/*\r\n        * Fix for ZF-8193\r\n        * Zend_Controller_Action->getInvokeArg('bootstrap') doesn't work\r\n        * under the unit testing environment.\r\n        *\/\r\n        if($front->getParam('bootstrap') === null)\r\n        {\r\n\t    $front->setParam('bootstrap', $this);\r\n        }\r\n\t\r\n        return $front;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n<\/code>",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=breich",
                        "name": "breich",
                        "displayName": "Brian Reich",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-15T07:48:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-15T07:48:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37220",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=elazar",
                        "name": "elazar",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Turland",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The issue is that Zend_Test_PHPUnit_ControllerTestCase doesn't call Zend_Application::run() anywhere. That method is responsible for calling Zend_Application_Bootstrap_Bootstrap::run(), which in turn calls Zend_Controller_Front::setParam() to store a reference to the bootstrap in the front controller as an invoking parameter. I believe Zend_Test_PHPUnit_ControllerTestCase should be modified, likely either in its bootstrap() method or its dispatch() method, to handle this.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=elazar",
                        "name": "elazar",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Turland",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-29T10:55:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-13T08:24:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37673",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Resolved in trunk with r20256.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-13T08:19:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-13T08:19:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42762",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=miholeus",
                        "name": "miholeus",
                        "displayName": "miholeus",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Not resolved in last release versions",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=miholeus",
                        "name": "miholeus",
                        "displayName": "miholeus",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-10-28T00:37:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-10-28T00:37:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42765",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actually, it is. Based on what you reported in ZF-10607, you were setting up your testing bootstrap incorrectly.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-10-28T05:38:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-10-28T05:38:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45834",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimuel",
                        "name": "zimuel",
                        "displayName": "Enrico Zimuel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm checking with ZF 1.11.3 and seems that the issue is still present. Here my code of testing:\r\n\r\n{code:none}\r\nclass ControllerTestCase\r\nextends Zend_Test_PHPUnit_ControllerTestCase {\r\n  \r\n  protected $application;\r\n  \r\n  public function setUp() \r\n  {\r\n    $this->bootstrap= array($this, 'appBootstrap');\r\n    parent::setUp();\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  public function appBootstrap()\r\n  {\r\n    $this->application= new Zend_Application(\r\n      APPLICATION_ENV,\r\n      APPLICATION_PATH.'\/configs\/application.ini'\r\n    );\r\n    $this->application->bootstrap();\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\nand the following testCase:\r\n{code:none}\r\nclass IndexControllerTest extends ControllerTestCase\r\n{\r\n  public function testBootstrap()\r\n  {\r\n    $this->dispatch('\/');\r\n    $this->assertType('Zend_Application_Bootstrap_Bootstrap', $this->_frontController->getParam('bootstrap'));\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\nThat fails.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimuel",
                        "name": "zimuel",
                        "displayName": "Enrico Zimuel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-04-07T16:04:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-04-07T16:07:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46505",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This issue seems to be triggered by this blog post (possibly among others): http:\/\/ailoo.net\/2009\/04\/set-up-a-zend-framework-application-using-zend_application-including-phpunit-setup\/\r\n\r\nI commented on that post hoping that Matthias will adjust the example.\r\n\r\nA correct setup for your tests looks like this:\r\n{code}\r\n    public function setUp()\r\n    {\r\n        $this->bootstrap = new Zend_Application(\r\n            APPLICATION_ENV,\r\n            APPLICATION_PATH . '\/configs\/application.ini'\r\n        );\r\n\r\n        parent::setUp();\r\n    }\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThis is taken from Matthew's example in the related issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-05-08T21:20:30.000+0000",
